
[1]diaphoretic

   DIAPHORETIC, a. [supra.] Having the power to increase perspiration;
   sudorific; sweating.

   DIAPHORETIC, n. A medicine which promotes perspiration; a sudorific.
   Diaphoretics differ from sudorifics; the former only increase the
   insensible perspiration; the latter excite the sensible discharge
   called sweat.
